HSBC Chief May Cut Middle-Management Jobs, Financial Times Says

-- B y   N a n d i n i   S u k u m a r
-- 
2011-04-23T13:53:39Z

-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2011-04-23/hsbc-chief-may-cut-middle-management-jobs-financial-times-says.html
HSBC Holdings Plc (HSBA)  Chief Executive
Officer  Stuart Gulliver  may cut middle-management jobs, the
Financial Times reported, citing people familiar with Gulliver’s
thinking.  A consulting firm hired to help with a review has
identified ways to streamline the bank’s operating structure,
the paper said.  To contact the editor responsible for this story:
Andrew Rummer at 
 arummer@bloomberg.net  